<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-07-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-07-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="462" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d462">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 5931/46.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Chargé <persName type="to">de Billier</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-07-22"><hi rend="italic">July 22,
                                1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Knox instructs Mr. de Billier to notify the minister for foreign
                            affairs of Persia that the legation is ready to enter into full
                            relations with the Government of the new Shah, and to express to him the
                            wishes of the American Government for the prosperity and tranquillity of
                            Persia under this rule.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>